er%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20someone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-family-cant-pronounce-my-name-correctly-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emisspells%20my%20name%20in%20an%20email%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20can%20still%20hear%20those%20snickers%20in%20my%20head%3A%20Jasley.%20Jaselyn.%20Joselyn.%20Jas.%20Jaselley.%20All%20loud%20and%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f1c5eb53-60b5-423e-96b0-280138aafe7e%5C%22%3EI%20feel%20disrespected%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20corporate%20world%2C%20we%20are%20frequently%20told%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskills-every-professional-should-have-2016-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euphold%20professionalism%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20all%20forms%20of%20communication.%20I%20was%20taught%20to%20double-%20and%20triple-check%20my%20emails%20for%20typos%20before%20sending%20them.%20I%20understood%20that%20misspelling%20someone's%20name%20was%20a%20sign%20of%20carelessness%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20disrespect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20digitally%20dot%20every%20I%20and%20cross%20every%20T%20in%20all%20my%20emails%2C%20just%20to%20receive%20a%20response%20saying%2C%20with%20random%20versions%20of%20what's%20supposed%20to%20be%20my%20name.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20name%20is%20in%20my%20email%2C%20signature%2C%20website%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoached-tech-job-linkedin-good-decision-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20bylines.%20It's%20exhausting.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20some%2C%20my%20request%20to%20spell%20my%20name%20correctly%20may%20seem%20dramatic.%20But%20I%20care.%20Many%20people%20from%20diverse%20backgrounds%20with%20unique%20names%20can%20relate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20%26quot%3Bjust%20a%20name%20%E2%80%94%26quot%3B%20it's%20my%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c12e242b-4980-44fd-99e8-5ff2e259efff%5C%22%3EI'm%20named%20after%202%20women%20in%20my%20family%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20named%20after%20two%20fearless%20and%20confident%20women%3A%20my%20mother%20and%20grandmother.%20My%20name%20is%20a%20combination%20of%20the%20first%20syllables%20of%20my%20mother's%20and%20grandmother's%20names%3A%20Jacqueline%20and%20Celina%2C%20with%20a%20special%20twist%20in%20its%20spelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20a%20nod%20to%20my%20Dominican%20culture%2C%20where%20it's%20common%20for%20mothers%20to%20create%20unique%20names%20by%20blending%20parts%20of%20loved%20ones'%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20name%20is%20prophetic%2C%20foreshadowing%20how%20I%20would%20navigate%20the%20world%3A%20fearlessly%20and%20confidently%2C%20just%20like%20my%20mother%20and%20grandmother.%20I%20wear%20my%20name%2C%20its%20unique%20pronunciation%20and%20spelling%20with%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20yes%2C%20it%20is%20deep%20to%20me.%20That's%20why%20I'm%20also%20intentional%20about%20extending%20the%20same%20care%20to%20others%20with%20names%20that%20reflect%20their%20culture%2C%20language%2C%20and%20proud%20lineage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20resonate%20deeply%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshonda-rhimes-murder-mystery-the-residence-netflix-release-date-cast-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Residence%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20actor%20Uzo%20Aduba's%20quote%20on%20her%20own%20name%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20mom%20taught%20me%20not%20to%20change%20my%20name%20for%20those%20unwilling%20to%20learn%20it.%20If%20they%20can%20learn%20to%20say%20Tchaikovsky%2C%20Dostoyevsky%2C%20and%20Michelangelo%2C%20they%20can%20learn%20to%20say%20Uzoamaka.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20long%20time%2C%20I%20didn't%20fully%20grasp%20the%20weight%20of%20that%20statement.%20Back%20in%20school%2C%20I%20would%20shy%20away%20from%20correcting%20my%20teachers.%20I%20used%20to%20feel%20embarrassed.%20However%2C%20as%20an%20adult%2C%20I've%20learned%20to%20reclaim%20the%20beauty%20of%20my%20name%20and%20correct%20people%