Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20both%20the%20show%20and%20reality%2C%20Fortune%20was%20married%20by%20the%20time%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Gilded%20Age%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it%20didn't%20stop%20Peggy%20and%20Fortune%20from%20developing%20a%20relationship%20during%20season%20two.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJohn%20Sanders%20plays%20the%20famous%20(and%20problematic)%20architect%2C%20Stanford%20White.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stanford%20White%20gilded%20age%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6889126bf748d8c055f6778d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHBO%3B%20Hulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20ever%20walked%20around%20Washington%20Square%20Park%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20you've%20seen%20one%20of%20White's%20most%20renowned%20pieces%20of%20work%3A%20the%20Washington%20Square%20Arch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20show%2C%20White%20is%20also%20responsible%20for%20designing%20the%20Russells'%20behemoth%20of%20a%20townhouse%20on%20Fifth%20Avenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20real%20life%2C%20White%20was%20involved%20in%20one%20of%20the%20era's%20biggest%20scandals.%20When%20he%20was%2048%2C%20he%20was%20accused%20of%20drugging%20and%20sexually%20assaulting%2016-year-old%20Evelyn%20Nesbit%2C%20a%20model%20and%20actor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201905%2C%20when%20Nesbit%20was%2021%2C%20she%20married%20another%20prominent%20New%20York%20figure%2C%20Henry%20Kendall%20Thaw.%20When%20Thaw%20learned%20what%20White%20had%20done%20to%20his%20wife%2C%20he%20murdered%20him%20during%20a%20performance%20at%20Madison%20Square%20Garden%20(a%20building%20he%20designed).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subsequent%20trial%20was%20a%20media%20circus%20and%20was%20even%20dubbed%20the%20trial%20of%20the%20century.%20Public%20opinion%20of%20White%20plummeted%20during%20the%20trial%20when%20the%20public%20learned%20about%20his%20private%20life.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1996%2F01%2F26%2Farts%2Fmurder-madness-and-mayhem.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Vanity%20Fair%20even%20ran%20this%20headline%3A%20%26quot%3BStanford%20White%2C%20Voluptuary%20and%20Pervert%2C%20Dies%20the%20Death%20of%20a%20Dog.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThaw%20was%20found%20not%20guilty%20by%20reason%20of%20insanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EClara%20Barton%2C%20as%20played%20by%20Linda%20Emond%2C%20appeared%20in%20the%20first%20season.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22clara%20barton%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688912b185e81483682ede12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHBO%3B%20Smith%20Collection%2FGado%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20season%20one%2C%20Marian%20(Louisa%20Jacobson)%20takes%20her%20aunts%20to%20a%20talk%20being%20given%20by%20Barton%2C%20a%20Civil%20War%20nurse%2C%20voting%20rights%20and%20equal%20rights%20activist%2C%20and%20key%20member%20of%20the%20American%20Red%20Cross.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJ.%20P.%20Morgan%2C%20as%20played%20by%20Bill%20Camp%2C%20joined%20the%20cast%20in%20season%20three.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jp%20morgan%20gilded%20age%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688913ec85e81483682ede44%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHBO%3B%20Bettman%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20Morgan%20was%20considered%20the%20greatest%20banker%20who%20ever%20lived%2C%20so%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20surprising%20that%20George%2C%20in%20need%20of%20capital%2C%20would%20turn%20to%20him%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJordan%20Waller%20played%20Oscar%20Wilde%20in%20a%20season%20two%20episode.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%